        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 6 at 6:53PM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 652 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Rochester, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Rochester, Akron, Mentone, Fulton, Beaver Dam Lake, Sevastopol, Nyena
Lake, Beaver Dam, Lake Manitou, Athens, Talma, and Marshtown.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
